Here are some key facts about the towns of Palu and Donggala on Sulawesi:
Palu is the capital of Central Sulawesi province, located at the end of a narrow bay on the western coast of Sulawesi island, with an estimated population of 379,800 people in 2017.
The city was celebrating its 40th anniversary when it was hit by an earthquake and tsunami.
Donggala is a regency stretching over 300 km (180 mi) along the coast of the northwest island of Sulawesi.
